<p style="text-align: left;">1. On 64-bit versions of Windows, Internet Explorer (32-bit) is recommended.<br>
2. Windows XP Professional limits the number of concurrent network connections to 10 (Home Edition limits concurrent connections to 5).<br>
3. Windows Vista limits the number of concurrent network connections to 10 (Home Basic and Home Premium Editions limit concurrent connections to 5).<br>
4. “Core Server Installation” of Windows Server 2008 is not supported.<br>
5. IIS needs to be enabled.</p>
